---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import silasPic from "../img/silas.jpg";
---

<Layout title="Silas Hsu">
	<main class="pt-8 md:flex gap-4">
		<div class="bg-slate-100 p-4 mb-8 flex flex-row md:flex-col gap-8 items-center md:items-start md:w-64 md:flex-none">
			<Image src={silasPic} alt="Silas Hsu" class="w-32 sm:w-56" style="border-radius: 50%" />
			<div>
				<p><b>Silas Hsu</b></p>
				<p>Assistant Professor</p>
				<p class="mb-6 text-sm">California Polytechnic State University, San Luis Obispo</p>
				<dl class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4 text-sm">
					<dt>Email</dt>
					<dd>sihsu [at] calpoly.edu</dd>
					<dt>Github</dt>
					<dd>
						<a href="https://github.com/smhsu" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600">smhsu</a>
					</dd>
					<dt>Office</dt>
					<dd>14-206</dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="p-4 md:mt-12">
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Hello!</h1>
			<p class="mb-4">
				Iâ€™m an Assistant Professor of Computer Science at CalPoly San Luis Obispo.  Before joining CalPoly, I
				was a PhD student at the University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign.
			</p>
			<p class="mb-4">
				I work in <b>Human-Computer Interaction</b>, especially (1) AI content curation
				systems (e.g. Facebook News Feed) and (2) AI feedback systems in education.  My research considers how
				these systems erode users' autonomy (e.g. how the systems fail to consider users' wishes with dignity),
				and examines what interface design decisions and regulations help resolve these issues.
			</p>
			<p class="mb-4">
				While I most often work on the interface design of AI systems, I'm also interested in and have done work
				in music education software and visualization tools for biologists.  Please contact me if you want
				to work with me in any of these areas!
			</p>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
